SIMPLE: choicely
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Choicely
<hw>Choice"ly</hw>, <pos>adv.</pos> <sn>1.</sn> <def>With care in
choosing; with nice regard to preference.</def> ⟦ldquo⟧A band of men
collected <xex>choicely</xex>, from each county some.⟦rdquo⟧
<rj><au>Shak.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>In a preferable or excellent manner; excellently;
eminently.</def> ⟦ldquo⟧<xex>Choicely</xex> good.⟦rdquo⟧
<rj><au>Walton.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Choiceness</ent>⟦br⟧
